                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Very nice post with many thoughtful ideas.  I hope SoE pays attention to this.
<br />

<br />
I'll add a stupid idea that I have that may not work at all.  It is to add a new illusion ability to the enchanters.
<br />

<br />
While a chanter goes into a mob infested terriotry, he may be able to do a "true" illusion, and transform himself into one of the mobs.  He will gain the mob's abilities in a reduced fashion.  While under this illusion, the enchanter will lose all of his own abilities.  This can make things a bit fun for the chanter, and make encanters more stackable in a group.
<br />

<br />
Some nights I saw two chanters LFG but no tank in sight.  Well then one of the two chanters can be somewhat of a tank in this case.  Tuning will have to be done so the chanter's illusion is not too powerful in this case.  As it stands, our charmed pet is usable as a tank, just with a very bad risk vs. reward situation.  With true illusion, the elimination of the chanter's other abilities including mezz, slow, etc. is a strong balance.
<br />

<br />
Of course, not all mobs can be "illusioned".  Some may even get angry at the chanter for trying to do so.    <img src="images/smiles/icon_mrgreen.gif" alt="icon_mrgreen.gif" border="0" />   Just a wild idea that I'm sure will need a lot of refinement.  But illusion is something that enchanters are good at.  And the fun factor of this ability may make chanters happy.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
