<br />

<br />
Well, firstly, if you monkey with mana regen rates, especially something as radical as halving it, they would need to do a massive re-evaluation of content (not that they don't need to already). Content was designed with current available mana regen rates in mind. Also, casting expenditures have been balanced (per se) around available mana regen rates. Besides, I am not sure how changing mana regen rates improves balance.
<br />

<br />
I know you will disagree with me, but if you make runes any more powerful, I believe it could alter significantly group and raid tactics. Couple this with ideas to make chanters 'exceptional' at getting hit, and I am sure it will cause balance problems.
<br />

<br />
I am also not too sure you want to spread mez around more. Folks have already complained about class dilution. Plus, unless you modify the abilities of classes who specialize in pulling, I am not sure how you can force in camp CC anyway. It is more complicated than just doling out mez.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But the question is what purpose does it serve in the balance of EQ?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
