That was the idea of spreading out mez.  The endurance/mana based mitigation abilities are designed to help with pre-slow tanking and add-tanking.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Wybart wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I'm not sure I get how MoM would work. Do you mean that it would be possible to always have MoM up? Or would you make it a spell? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Yes, it would mean an enchanter could always have MoM up.  Leave it as an AA.
<br />

<br />
The ratios (2:1, 2.5:1, 3:1) where set up based off the assumption that MoM L 1 would be something you bought as you leveled, and MoM 2 and 3 wouldn't be HUGELY different, but good enough to easily justify the extra AA.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Wybart wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Another idea to get rid of the "mob-hits-like-freight-train-on-inc but gimp-when-slowed" would be to add a 'rage factor' to each mob. On initial aggro, the mob does its (low) base damage, and during the first 30 seconds its rage will build each second (or tick) and increase its damageoutput to its intended peak (like 2xbase).</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
You could also do this based off mob damage, like summoning.
<br />

<br />
At 90% health, a mob gets "angry", and it's damage increases 50%. (to current levels)
<br />
At 40% health, a mob "surges", and it's damage goes up by 5% per second over 10 seconds. (to higher-than-current levels)
<br />

<br />
This would increase the utility of "spike DPS" over "sustained DPS", and makes back-end damage more useful.
<br />

<br />
This would allow more divergence between the sustained DPS dealers and spike DPS classes.  However, they'd have to provide raid content that rewarded sustained DPS: currently raids are far to much about spike DPS, which has lead to rogue sustained DPS reaching near wizard spike DPS levels.
<br />

<br />
In this day and age, nobody cares about spike DPS in XP groups.
<br />

<br />
It would also make adds less dangerous to a greater degree than it would make single creatures less dangerous.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Badmorda wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I think most of the suggestions Yakk has would cause more problems than it solves, except for the mez soft cap thing.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
