Agreed.  The goal, however, is to make buffing <span style="font-weight: bold">less</span> important.  Players should be sought out for active, fun, roles.
<br />

<br />
The fact that buffing is currently so powerful means that either buffing classes are overpowered, or they are inactive.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Badmorda wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">If you up the rune amount with a focus, you do improve it's efficiency. I still believe that a rune is much better at dealing with spike damage than a heal, so, in some situations, combining the two would (and this is just my theory) exponentionally increase the power of the group/raid. I could be wrong, but I really feel that is what would happen.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
