                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I really think that druids, who can charm animals, should also be allowed to mez them.  Mages should get an elemental mez, necros should get an undead mez.
<br />

<br />
From what I can see, those classes tend to suffer quite abit from poor grouping abilities, although druids and even necros have had some improvements in that area lately. 
<br />

<br />
In my opinion, if you can charm something, why can't you mez it?  From a purely design point of view, I see charm as a more powerful form of control than mez.
<br />

<br />
I definately agree that enchanters need to be more survivable.  I hate what they've done to charm, but if thats the way its gonna be to lower our offense, then fine... at least enable us to survive the mob when it breaks.  
<br />

<br />
Everquest is not supposed to be a "twitch-game", where hitting a button faster, or at just the right time, makes you a better player.  It should be more about timing, coordination, and teamwork.  When mobs can take out people in less than 10 seconds... and the mobs con blue... thats becomming more and more arcade-like, and I honestly hope that the people who design the future of everquest are aware of that. 
<br />

<br />
I understand the difficulties in extending content and scaling up a game.  Players need to feel that they are continually growing, becomming bigger, better, etc.  Without room to grow, the game becomes pretty boring for many types of players.  The problem with this, is that everquest does not scale linearly.  Those who have played eq since its release, have a very clear picture of that. 
<br />

<br />
I don't want to be considered "good" because I can press a button faster than someone else.  Everquest is a mental game, not a physical one.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tashim</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.botsguild.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
