Illusions have never been more than an occasional utility for the class.  Indeed, I'm hard pressed to come up with ways that they could be made 'useful' without being made excessive.  A mana regen illusion would be on everyone, all the time, and that would be lame.  We already have a melee boost illusion, and most melee I know won't take it because it's 'annoying'.  
<br />

<br />
Anything that can be done with an illusion can be done in a generally less irritating fashion with a spell that lacks an illusion component.  If you want to dress up our balancing spells in illusions, that's fine, but first you have to find out what those spells will BE.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
