Agreed.
<br />

<br />
The 3:1 ratio was pretty much pulled out of my ass.  =)  10 seconds of a 900 DPS mob is 3000-odd mana, something you can deal with once every 3 minutes.
<br />

<br />
I originally had a more complicated version (1 damage:mana, but 66% of the mana stolen was returned over time -- basically, 2/3 of the mana spent would be moved into a seperate buffer, which drained back into your mana pool), with the goal to make mana capacity as important as HP capacity.  I still suspect this might be a good idea, but it is much wierder.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Khyla the Apathetic wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I like a lot of the idea of the buff shift, but it does have some impact on soloin and we need to think of how to adress that to try to reflect balance as they have it now. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
