</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Fian2 wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The rest of the ideas are too extreme for me - I prefer changes in the mobs that we fight instead of changing enchanters.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I am holding that the other classes have changed so much that the mobs had to change to follow suit.
<br />

<br />
Plate tanks mitigate damage so much better than other classes nowadays it isn't funny.  I even agree with it!  It was better than a HP-gap.  But, if enchanters want to be a class-that-gets-hit, they need to be able to be hit.
<br />

<br />
Scaling down mobs to the point where enchanters have no problems getting hit make the mobs trivial for plate tanks to deal with.  Maybe this would also be of benefit -- but it means that the era of "mob difficulty = mob reward" goes away.
<br />

<br />
Remember when rewards where all about rare spawns?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Fian2 wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I also like having buffs that people want. On the other hand, if EQ ever seriously wants to promote soloing, they will need to do something to improve the regen rate for casters.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
How much power are you willing to give up for buffs that people want?  If they want to balance EQ, one's passive buff power and one's active power have to add to be the same as everyone else.
<br />

<br />
Either they add a tonne of passive buff power to every other class, we are gimpy at actively doing stuff, they make our buffs less important, or they make the game out of balance with overly powerful classes.
<br />

<br />
Thank you all for the comments!
<br />

<br />
I am also of the opinion that they can do negative things to the enchanter class at the same time -- or pseudo negative things.
<br />

<br />
For example, readd the stun component to our non-ancient line of nukes.  This makes our DPS riskier and harder to use (extra aggro from the stun).
<br />

<br />
Possibly give enchanters a fast casting high-damage stun-nuke as our next non-ancient nuke, like really old-school enchanter nukes where, but leave the recast tied.  This would result in a minimal increase in sustained or burst DPS, but stun nukes that are fast casting are more useful.
<br />

<br />
On the other hand, the above does reduce the passive power of an enchanter in the group (haste and slow).</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Yakk on Mon Feb 28, 2005 11:35 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
